node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Lets Talk Mental Health in Santa Monica, California with @letstalk.mentalhealth. May be an image of text that says 'CONDITIONAL LOVE UNCONDITIONAL LOVE -Selfish -Seeks control -Selfless -Seeks freedom -Has expectations -Criticizes -No expectations -Jealous -Seeks understanding -Secure -"Keeps score" -Works as a team -Minimize partners needs -Supports partners needs @letstalk.mentalhealth'.

node.text:
Conditional love doesn’t feel very nice. In fact, it doesn’t always feel like love at all. When someone loves us conditionally, it means that they put terms, restrictions, or rules on the giving of their love. While a person can have feelings of deep care or affection for you, their love is conditional if it feels like you have to earn it. These can sometimes overlap a bit, but generally this list is a good starting point 🗣🔥

#conditionallove #unconditionallove #love #abuse #freedom #control #mentalhealthawareness #support #relationshipgoals #mentalhealth

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Lets Talk Mental Health on September 16, 2021 tagging @letstalk.mentalhealth. May be an image of text that says 'SIGNS YOU MIGHT BE IN SURVIVAL MODE Help! @letstalk.mentalhealth'.

node.text:
Have you ever heard of flight, fight, or freeze? During times of crisis, chaos, and traumatic experiences we enter “survival mode.” You might have heard this phrase before; but what does it mean? When we experience stressful events our brains being to function in a different capacity. It is important to mention that these experiences can either be real life threats or perceived treats to our safety; our brain does not always differentiate between them, it just reacts 

Finding ways to self-sooth, find support, and calm your nervous system is key 🗣🔥

#survivalmode #trauma #mentalhealth #mentalhealthawareness #survival #mode #abuse #stress #anxiety #fear

Sources: CGRG, Psychologytoday

node.text:
Narcissistic abuse is a form of emotional abuse perpetrated by someone who suffers from narcissism or sociopathy. These individuals have a tendency – whether conscious or unconscious – to use words and language in manipulative ways to damage, alter, or otherwise control their partner’s behaviour.

While all narcissistic abuse generally falls under the description of ‘thought control’ or ‘emotional manipulation,’ there are several ways that narcissists tend to go about this. Some narcissists use manipulative techniques like gaslighting to confuse and disorient their partners so they become more susceptible to their demands and their abuse.

Victims often feel they can’t trust their own thoughts or sense of reality. 

I think it’s also important to note that not all people who have NPD abuse other people. Many people who have NPD work to understand themselves and are not malicious with their intentions 🗣🔥

Sources: psychologytoday, rosglasrecovery, choosingtherapy

node.text:
I wanted to provide a really clear diagram of what social anxiety can feel like as many of us experience it to some extent

Please comment what resonates most with you. 

For me, it’s shaky voice and leaving early. One remedy I use to calm my voice is to humm when I feel my social anxiety kicking it. It helps relax the voice and people have used humming for centuries to calm down. 

Please share any tips you have 🗣🔥
